Bring a #large saucepan{} of water to the boil with a pinch of @salt{}. Preheat your #oven{} to 200°C. Pour a large glug of @olive oil{} into a #roasting tray{}. Pop it onto the top shelf of your oven to warm up. Put a small drizzle of @olive oil{} in the bottom of another #baking tray{}, pop the @pork roasting joint{450%g} in the baking tray and sprinkle over half the @cumin seeds{1/2} and @salt and @pepper. Roast in the middle of your oven for ~{45-60%minutes} (depending on size). 

> IMPORTANT: The pork is cooked when no longer pink in the middle, wash your hands after handling raw meat.

Meanwhile, peel the @potatoes{900%g} and chop into 4cm chunks. Add them to the boiling water and cook for ~{7-8%minutes} or until the edges have softened when you poke them with a knife. Once the potatoes are ready, drain in a #colander{}, pop back into the pan then sprinkle on half the @plain flour{12%g}. Give your pan a shake to fluff up the potato. Take your hot baking tray out of your oven, carefully transfer your potatoes onto it in a single layer. Sprinkle over a pinch of salt and gently turn the potatoes so they're coated in oil. Roast the potatoes on the top shelf of your oven for ~{45-50%minutes}, turning halfway through.

Trim the @chantenay carrots{250%g} and halve lengthways. Quarter the @apple{1} (no need to peel) and remove the core. Chop each quarter into 2 wedges. Pop them in a #bowl{} and add the @honey{15%ml} and remaining @cumin seeds{1/2}. Add a drizzle of @olive oil{}, a pinch of salt and pepper and mix together.

When the pork has 25 mins left. Add the carrots and apple to the baking tray to roast with the pork until soft, ~{25%minutes}. Meanwhile, halve, peel and thinly slice the @echalion shallot{1}. Grate the @mature cheddar cheese{60%g}. Refill your #saucepan{} with water and pop on to boil - we will use it to cook the broccoli later.

== Gravy ==

Meanwhile, put a saucepan on medium heat and add half the @unsalted butter{15%g}. Allow the butter to melt, then stir in the remaining @plain flour{12%g}. You've made a roux! Cook, stirring constantly until the roux is a medium brown colour and gradually stir in the @water{} and @chicken stock paste{1}. Bring to the boil, stirring out any lumps that form. Lower the heat and simmer until the gravy has thickened to your liking, ~{15-20%minutes}, stir occasionally.

== Broccoli Cheese ==

Meanwhile, add the @broccoli florets{200%g} to the boiling water and simmer until just tender, ~{3%minutes}. Drain in a colander and pop into an #ovenproof dish{}. Pop your pan back on medium heat with the remaining @unsalted butter{15%g} (no need to wash). Add the @British smoked bacon lardons{60%g} and stir fry until browned, ~{3-5%minutes}. Add the shallot and fry until softened, ~{3%minutes}. Pour in the @creme fraiche{150%g}, @water{} and @Dijon mustard{1/2}. Add a pinch of salt and pepper. Bring to the boil, then remove from the heat and stir in ¾ of the cheese.

== Assembly ==

Pour the creamy sauce over the broccoli in the #dish{}. Mix the @panko breadcrumbs{25%g} with the remaining cheese, a pinch of salt and pepper and the @olive oil{}. Sprinkle the mixture on top, then bake in your oven until golden and bubbling, ~{10-15%minutes}.

Once the pork is ready, cover with #foil{} and leave to rest for ~{15%minutes}. Once everything is ready, reheat the gravy. Reheat the carrots and apple in the oven if necessary. Thinly slice the pork and serve on plates with the veggies. Add any resting juices to the gravy and pour over, Enjoy!